May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I don't want to bore you with my story so I'll keep it short. got laid off from my job in 2017, and there was nothing could do about it. started selling on Amazon because needed to put food on the table and had a kid on the way.'.

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on July 19, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I only ended up using $3k to start. I bought a course from some guy with a Lambo and it was clear that he didn't sell on Amazon. It didn't help much and had to learn everything from scratch.'.

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on July 19, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace Now to the fun part. I had three products fail before had one successful product. I took the every ast dollar made from that product and reinvested it back into the business. My family was even surviving off of credit card points at one point.'.

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on July 19, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I almost completely lost my business a few months later. I tried launching 2 products, and ran out of cash to buy inventory. I had to let go of both of my new products and refilled the inventory on my first product. I got too greedy and paid the price.'.

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on July 19, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace Since then, I've learned my lesson. Never scale too quickly an always take things one step at a time. I've been building this business for 3 years now and still reinvest 40% of my profits back into the business. Even after 3 years, it's barely gotten to the $100k/m profit point.'.

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on July 19, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace So what lessons can you take away from this? 1. Don't scale too quickly. 2. Don't overestimate your abilities. 3. Take things one step at a time. 4. Chasing short-term wins can hurt you long-term. 5. Learn from others who have done it, but always look for ways to improve.'.

Photo shared by All About Making Money 💸 on July 19, 2021 tagging @clintmwallace. May be an image of text that says 'Clint Wallace @clintmwallace I've built my Amazon FBA ousiness to $250k/ rev and $100k/m profit. If wasn't so focused on getting rich quick when started I'd probably be at $500k/m. Hopefully you don't make the same mistakes that made.'.
